/'  Full .stuff Syntax Showcase  '/
/'  ===========================  '/

#1 Introduction

This paragraph shows *bold* and _italic_ and ~strikethrough~.  
You can also escape special characters: \* \_ \~ \@ \& \\.

#2 Nested Blockquotes

> Level 1 blockquote with *bold* and _italic_.
>> Level 2 nested blockquote with ~strikethrough~.
>>> Level 3 nested with a reference to the next chunk: &+1

--- /' Horizontal rule separates sections '/

Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur.

#3 More Formatting

Here we have *bold* mixed with _italic_ and even ~strikethrough~ combined in one place.

>>> Triple nested blockquote with text inside that also has *bold* formatting

Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.

:>(my_quote_chunk)  /' give the previous blockquote a name '/

---
/' Lists '/
---
- Unordered item one
- Unordered item two with *bold*
  - Nested unordered item (indentation is not strict, but still a list item)
- Unordered item three

1. First ordered item
2. Second ordered item
3. Third ordered item with _italic_

---
/' Images '/
---
![ Alt text with _italic_ | https://example.com/logo.png ]

![| /local/image.jpg]  /' no alt text '/

---
/' Directives '/
---

@simple_directive    /' no arguments '/
@plugin(arg1, &my_quote_chunk)   /' passes a named chunk '/
@toc(&-1, &+1)   /' passes previous and next chunks '/

---
/' Chunks '/
---

This is an anonymous implicit chunk.

This is another implicit chunk, which will be named. :>(my_named_chunk)

:<
This is an explicit chunk.
It can contain multiple blocks, like this paragraph and the next heading.

#4 Inside Explicit Chunk

And a list inside the explicit chunk:
- item a
- item b

>:(inside_explicit)   /' end of explicit chunk '/

---
/' References in text '/
---
You can refer to the previous chunk with &-1, the next with &+1, or a named one like &my_named_chunk.

---
/' Escaping '/
---
Literal characters: \@ is not a directive, \* is not bold, \& is not a reference.

/' End of showcase '/
